metadata.name: Multi-Biome #76
metadata.description:
Inspired by Jose Margulis's "Alpine Landscape"

Designed to be viewed as if you're walking past on the gallery wall, Multi-Biome is an interative play on perspective and scale. Each landscape is created from between 50 and 200 planes, slicing the landscape along a single axis.

Click and drag to rotate.

Press "s" in live view to save a png.

metadata.name: EAMES #9
metadata.description:
Inspired by the cover of ‘Mid-Century Modern Design: A Complete Sourcebook’, an algorithm draws a random assortment of semi-circles. It then renders a collection of diamonds that are accented with dots and triangles. 

Initially written in TypeScript and transpiled into 66.9 KB of JavaScript.




ABOUT THE ARTIST

RepRage draws upon experience gained as a classically trained software engineer to imbue software with the warmth of our analog past.

metadata.name: RADII #64
RADII #67
RADII #69
SkeleSteamPunx #94
metadata.description:
Genesis generative image project by @LimnDigital.

65 total unique traits = 2,459,688 possible variations (including backgrounds and base)
52 skull/facial traits = 111,804 possible variations. 
Each trait created via custom VQGAN+CLIP Python code by LimnDigital.
Each trait isolated and manually extracted in Procreate, then randomly assembled via p5.js and custom JavaScript by LimnDigital.

Not associated with Larva Labs, CryptoPunks, or any ‘Skulls’ or ‘Punks’ projects. 

Save your minted Artwork (or any edition) in Live Mode by pressing:
‘s’ or ‘S’ to save at current canvas size.
‘f’ or ‘F’ to save at Full size, 2048 x 2048px.
‘t’ or ‘T’ to save at Twitter Tweet size, 1200 x 1200px.

Saved Artwork filename contains: Project Name, Artist Name, Pixel size, and Unique Hash.

metadata.name: Traces #66
metadata.description:
Traces is an exploration around movement.
Inspired but motion blur in photography, using lines travelling through obstacles, it can create scenes, sometimes representation of virtual landscapes.

Its features include:
- A choice between 12 modern and 7 rarer palette inspired by some of my photographies (revealed on my twitter with the first mint
- 3 definitions
- 3 types of obstacles modifying the motion
- Rare symmetrical dispositions

The art is better viewed in full screen, captures don't display the fine details

Unsold will be burnt after a certain time, and price might increase

metadata.description:

metadata.name: Fabrics #878
metadata.description:
Fabric. A collection of swatches. 

This is a project of stacked PNGs producing fabric swatches. Some are almost plaids, others are more batik, while others are more of a "magic eye" or optical illusion look. 

The PNGs were generated using VBA and conditional formatting in MS Excel, then copy/pasted as an image into MS PowerPoint, and occasionally further manipulated in different image editors including MS Paint. Images were batch resized to match each other at 1125x1125.

There are a lot of options for this collection. The layers and total number of options per (included "none" layers):
- Base
    - 42
- Flecking 
    - 18
- Broad
    - 50
- Underpin
    - 43
- Warp
    - 21
- Weft
    - 26
- Overpins
    - 43
- Mask
    - 21
- Texture
    - 14


There is a slight potential to mint the "imaginary fabric", one which is comprised of only "none" layers. That is the best of the bunch, because it is only limited by your imagination. Consider it the legendary.

There should be an interplay between the coded elements of each individual PNG and the overall stack. The randomness of coded layers stacked with other, dissimilar (base) coded layers generates interesting, and at times, colorful patterns that don't have a singular, obvious, overarching algo.

Hope you enjoy! 

Stacking achieved using PureSpider's pfp code https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

License CC BY-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Werckmeister Harmonies #68
metadata.description:
Inspired by the opening scene of the 'Werckmeister Harmonies' movie. This artwork was created with P5.js and variation functions, mostly used Peter de Jong's map equations. Many thanks to tsulej's article, 'Folds', which helped me to understand the variation functions.

Werckmeister Harmonies comes with different colors, the most rarest is the inverted B&W.

Bálint Kulcsár, 2022
